8. Conclusion
WIND-BORN events are best described as witness-class intermediary phenomena arising under 
threshold stress, characterized by perimeter attendance, geometry shift, and linguistic cost. Their 
defining feature is not what they “do,” but what they make possible—and what they make 
expensive (naming, certainty, story).
